  "script": "A plane crashed at takeoff! A Pilatus PC-6 Porter — ten skydivers and their pilot — lifted off from Nancy-Essey airfield in northeastern France on Sunday morning. Three hundred meters out, it came straight down. All eleven died. Families on the ground watched it happen. The five novice jumpers were nurses, there on a work celebration, jumping for the first time. Five instructors. One pilot. The plane had climbed maybe 100 feet when it went almost vertical and didn't come back up. French aviation investigators have grounded all PC-6 Porters while they figure out why. It's the deadliest skydiving crash France has seen in thirty years. What exactly went wrong in the first 300 meters?",
